Your project is on **MSTest v3 (3.8.0)** targeting **net8.0** — the TFM is fine for v4.

## Breaking changes that affect YOUR code

**`[ExpectedException]` removed** (lines 9, 16) — this is the main issue. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>` inside the test body:

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

Same pattern for `Process_InvalidState_ThrowsInvalidOperation`.

## Other v4 breaking changes to watch for (not in your current code)

| Change | Fix |
|---|---|
| `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` removed | Use `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>` |
| `TestMethodAttribute("name")` won't compile | Use `DisplayName = "name"` |
| `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed | Remove the argument from `[ClassCleanup]` |
| `TestContext.Properties.Contains()` | Use `.ContainsKey()` |
| `TestTimeout.Infinite` removed | Use `int.MaxValue` |
| Custom `TestMethodAttribute.Execute` | Override `ExecuteAsync` instead |

## Key behavioral changes

- **`TestCase.Id` changed** — Azure DevOps test history may reset
- **`TreatDiscoveryWarningsAsErrors`** defaults to `true` — discovery warnings now fail
